 ## Custom Proposer Backend (Experimental)
 
 You can plug in your own custom proposer class for speculative decoding by setting the method to `custom_class` and providing the full module path to your class.
-Your custom class must accept a `VllmConfig` upon instantiation and implement a `propose` method.
+Your custom class must accept a `VllmConfig` upon instantiation and implement
+either the legacy `propose` method or `propose_with_context`.
+
+`propose_with_context` receives a
+`vllm.v1.spec_decode.custom_class_proposer.CustomProposerContext`. The
+versioned context exposes request IDs and per-request speculation budgets,
+CPU token history, GPU-resident sampled tokens, target hidden states, sampling
+and verifier metadata, scheduler output, and KV slot mappings. These objects
+are borrowed from the model runner for the duration of the call; custom
+proposers must not mutate or retain them. Check `context.api_version` before
+using version-specific fields.
+
+The legacy `propose(sampled_token_ids, num_tokens_no_spec, token_ids_cpu,
+slot_mappings=...)` form remains supported. It runs after CPU bookkeeping and
+does not receive target-side GPU tensors.
 
 **Example configuration:**
 
